Class RuleOperatingMode

java.lang.Object
  |
  +--sentinel.led.RuleOperatingMode
class RuleOperatingMode
extends java.lang.Object

This class contains symbolic constants that are used denote the status of an executing rule. These are used when the rules are scheduled for execution by the rule scheduler. Once a rule is scheduled, it will be in one of these operating modes until it finishes execution.
